title: Great Parks of Africa
subTitle: The Addo Elephant Park was founded in 1931 and is 1,640km2. It hosts more than 450 elephants and other mammals and was created in response to the elephant population falling as low as eleven.

title: Great Parks of Africa
subTitle: Table Mountain National Park on the southwestern tip of Africa surrounded by ocean and humanity. It is a rugged peninsula jutting out into the cold Atlantic Ocean and forming an island of incredible diversity.

title: Great Parks of Africa
subTitle: In the northeastern corner of South Africa lays a land of unparalleled beauty that encompasses pristine beaches and vibrant coral reefs, lush wetlands and lakes, and vast forests and open plains. Each landscape provides sanctuary for a range of animals. Known locally as the Miracle, due to its beauty, this is the magical world of iSimangaliso.

title: Great Parks of Africa
subTitle: In the centre of South Africa is an ancient landscape that was once an inland sea. Now it is a mosaic of unique habitats. Life here has evolved ingenious solutions to survive. There is nowhere in South Africa quite like the Karoo National Park.

title: Pride Rules
subTitle: Come full circle as the dry season descends and the Waterfront Pride enjoys good hunting and renewed confidence in their territory. Then celebrate the success of former outsider Einstein, who gets down to business as the king of his very own pride.

title: Tigerfish: Africa's Piranha
subTitle: Tigerfish are terrifying freshwater predators. Extreme angler Andy Coetzee undertakes a hazardous journey to study the giant-sized species in their habitat in the Congo.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: There are many fine examples of evolutionary history in the natural world. Animals adapt through a series of small, random mutations and usually do so in order to compete more effectively for food, water and space. Crocodiles are certainly of an ancient lineage, they are believed to be 200 million years old. Sharks have gone through the process of adaptation and evolutionary experimentation as well.

title: Sons of Enkai
subTitle: An intimate look at the relationship between man and nature in one of the most iconic wild places on Earth: the Masai Mara, Kenya. A Maasai warrior guides viewers through natural epic events and spectacular wildlife.

title: Big Cat Tales
subTitle: Chongo is unwilling to share buffalo with the rest of the pride and Fig continues to give vital lessons to the young cub and a cheetah and hyena battle.

title: Animal Armory
subTitle: Cuttlefish and squid eject a black fluid to help them hide from predators, while skunks aren't the only animals to use scent glands for defence.

title: The new animal kingdom Japan
subTitle: Winter has gripped the north of Honshu and Hokkaido. The fox and its partner are expecting a litter of cubs, but it is difficult to find food. They each go their own way in search of food.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: A showcase of some of wildlife's most remarkable moments, caught on film by amateurs and professionals. We reveal the full spectrum of animal behaviour: the brutal, the beautiful and the bizarre. Each moment is explained by experts in the field.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: African rainforests, which are among the oldest in the world and are inhabited by some of the most legendary animals including gorillas, chimpanzees and okapi.

title: Okavango: River of Dreams
subTitle: Follows the life of lioness Fekeetsa as she travels around her territory in the Upper Okavango river.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: Kamuti is a wise old leopard who has reigned over two square miles of prime territory in the Luangwa Valley for ten years, but now she is in trouble. At 13-years-old, Kamuti is one of the oldest leopards in the African bush, and she is not as effective a hunter as she used to be. Kamuti's problems are compounded by her neighbours, the Nsefu pride of lions, who steal her kills and attack her on sight.

title: Hot Life Africa
subTitle: Lion prey tends to feed when hunters are resting, which means when the sun is at its highest. A rise in temperature affects the behaviour of the animals living in these hot areas.

subTitle: For many animals, being able to transfer their genes is the most important reason for life.

subTitle: The filmmaker sheds light on a feline predator and her dramatic struggle for survival as she catches prey and feeds her young in the cold and unforgiving conditions.

subTitle: Velvet the Gaboon viper and Therma the rattlesnake are two mothers facing different challenges in extreme, contrasting landscapes.

subTitle: India's highly venomous snakes are over four metres long and widely feared, but little is known about them.

subTitle: An exploration of the Lower Okavango river and the various events that occur when it has run its course.

subTitle: Three of the pride's lionesses go into labour, but new cubs bring with them big danger, as three strong males are plotting to destroy their world from across Zambia's Luangwe River.

subTitle: Being thin, having black patches on light-coloured fur, hyperventilating and licking itself regularly to evaporate saliva are the cheetah's most effective tricks to cope with its scorching environment.

subTitle: Diverse animal species display unique resilience and behaviour, facing numerous challenges as they adapt and struggle to survive in the wild.

title: Birds Of Bihar
subTitle: Featuring the travel sojourn of migratory birds seeking refuge in the wetlands of Bihar. The various wetlands spanning across several districts in Bihar provide feeding and nesting grounds during the harsh northern winters to these migratory birds. Various breed of birds that flock to these regions. We also learn significant facts about them.

subTitle: The Marsh Pride of lions in Kenya's Maasai Mara Reserve. This tale of shifting loyalties, bloody takeovers and sheer resilience is told by those who filmed them for over 30 years.

subTitle: Males and females of some species fight viciously. Though they are usually not trying to kill each other, the fighting can result in death.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: With predators always looking for a meal, their prey must constantly avoid being eaten. Defensive adaptations add to their chances of survival.

title: Wildest Survival
subTitle: For every baby animal born, millions do not survive, whether because of drought, flood, famine or predators. Babies are born into a harsh world, and their parents go to extreme efforts to ensure the survival of their offspring.

title: Wild Dynasties
subTitle: Raising young is no easy task, but out in the wild, the threats to vulnerable youngsters are endless. It's up to the fearsome and tenacious mothers to find clever ways to make sure their babies survive to adulthood.
